{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019MGUNhcXUt12CxgVZsnvnv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Web UI Related Files - Complete Inventory\n\n### Summary\nThe Cloche project implements a comprehensive web dashboard with Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming for live log display. Here's the complete breakdown of all web UI related files:\n\n---\n\n## Files Found\n\n### **Core Web Infrastructure**\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** (49.1KB)\n   - Main HTTP request handler\n   - **SSE Streaming Handler**: `handleAPIStream()` (lines 805-871)\n     - Serves live log streams via Server-Sent Events\n     - Sets headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`\n     - Handles both active (live) and completed runs\n     - For active runs: subscribes to broadcaster and streams live events\n     - For completed runs: reads archived full.log file\n   - **Full Log Streaming**: `streamFullLog()` (lines 876-898)\n     - Reads `.cloche/{run-id}/output/full.log` files\n     - Parses log lines in format: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n     - Sends each line as SSE data event\n   - **Log Parsing**: \n     - `parseFullLogLine()` (lines 916-931): Parses structured log format with regex\n     - `parseLLMLogLine()` (lines 904-914): Parses Claude LLM stream JSON\n   - **Log regex pattern**: `^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$` (line 874)\n   - Route handler: `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`\n\n2. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`**\n   - **SSE Tests**:\n     - `TestSSE_CompletedRun_ServesFullLog()`: Tests archived log streaming\n     - `TestSSE_ActiveRun_StreamsLive()`: Tests live broadcaster streaming\n     - `TestSSE_RunNotFound()`: Tests 404 handling\n     - `TestSSE_NoBroadcaster_ActiveRun()`: Tests 503 when broadcaster unavailable\n     - `TestParseFullLogLine()`: Tests log line parsing\n     - `TestSSE_CompletedRun_NoFullLog()`: Tests runs without log files\n   - Validates `text/event-stream` Content-Type header\n   - Tests SSE event format with `event: done` terminal event\n\n3. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`**\n   - General web handler tests\n   - Includes mock container manager for testing\n\n### **HTML Templates**\n\n4. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html`**\n   - Master layout template\n   - Navbar with Cloche logo\n   - Loads CSS from `/static/style.css`\n   - Block sections for content and scripts\n\n5. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`** (KEY: Log Display)\n   - **Log Viewer Section** (lines 101-105):\n     ```html\n     <h2>Log\n         <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\">Live</span>\n     </h2>\n     <div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\"><pre id=\"log-content\"></pre></div>\n     ```\n   - **JavaScript SSE Client** (lines 108-352):\n     - **EventSource Connection** (line 142):\n       ```javascript\n       var source = new EventSource('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stream');\n       ```\n     - **Log Line Handler** (lines 126-134):\n       - `appendLogLine()`: Creates span elements for each log line\n       - CSS class: `log-line log-type-[type]`\n       - Format: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n     - **Auto-scroll Logic** (lines 118-124, 131-133):\n       - Tracks scroll position to enable/disable auto-scroll\n       - Checks if viewer is within 40px of bottom\n       - Auto-scrolls when new content arrives\n     - **Event Listeners**:\n       - `onmessage`: Receives log line events (default message handler)\n       - `addEventListener('done')`: Terminates stream and marks complete\n       - `onerror`: Closes stream on connection errors\n     - **Status Badge Updates** (lines 136-139, 159-162):\n       - Initially shows \"Live\" (running badge)\n       - Changes to \"Complete\" (succeeded badge) when done event received\n     - **Steps Polling** (lines 164-275):\n       - Polls `/api/runs/{id}` every 2 seconds for active runs\n       - Updates steps table with accordion-style expandable output rows\n       - Fetches individual step output from `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n     - **Container Status Updates** (lines 175-192):\n       - Polls for container state changes\n       - Displays running/stopped/available states\n     - **Run Control Functions**:\n       - `cancelRun()` (lines 286-303): POST to `/api/runs/{id}/stop`\n       - `deleteContainer()` (lines 306-324): DELETE to `/api/runs/{id}/container`\n\n6. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`**\n   - Displays list of all runs\n   - Project filter functionality\n   - **Polling Script** (line 167):\n     - Polls `/api/runs` every 3 seconds\n     - Groups runs with parent/child relationships\n     - Handles escaping of HTML in dynamic content\n\n7. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`**\n   - Project information panel\n   - Workflow visualization with DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph)\n   - Drawer-based step details view\n   - Fetches project data from `/api/projects/{name}/info`\n   - Workflow data from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n\n8. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`**\n   - Projects overview page\n   - Project health indicators\n   - Recent run history as dot indicators\n\n### **CSS Styling**\n\n9. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** (598 lines)\n   - **Log Viewer Styles** (lines 387-410):\n     ```css\n     .log-viewer {\n         background: var(--bg-surface);\n         border: 1px solid var(--border);\n         border-radius: var(--radius);\n         max-height: 600px;\n         overflow: auto;\n         margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n     }\n     .log-line { display: block; }\n     .log-type-status { color: var(--badge-running-text); }\n     .log-type-llm { color: var(--badge-succeeded-text); }\n     .log-type-script { color: var(--text); }\n     ```\n   - **Badge Animations** (lines 117-127):\n     - Running badge has pulsing animation\n   - **Theme Support** (lines 1-56):\n     - Light mode and dark mode CSS variables\n     - Responsive design at 768px breakpoint\n   - **Comprehensive Component Styling**:\n     - Tables, buttons, panels, tabs, drawer, DAG visualization\n     - Scrollable elements (.step-output, pre elements)\n\n### **Log Stream Infrastructure**\n\n10. **`/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`** (141 lines)\n    - **Broadcaster Pattern**:\n      - Thread-safe pub/sub for active run logs\n      - `Subscribe(runID)`: Creates subscriber with 256-element buffer\n      - `Publish(runID, line)`: Non-blocking publish (drops if buffer full)\n      - `Finish(runID)`: Marks run complete, closes all subscriber channels\n    - **LogLine Data Structure** (lines 7-13):\n      ```go\n      type LogLine struct {\n          Timestamp string\n          Type      string  // \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n          Content   string\n          StepName  string\n      }\n      ```\n\n11. **`/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`** (233 lines)\n    - **Claude LLM Stream Parsing**:\n      - `ParseClaudeLine()`: Parses individual Claude stream-json lines\n      - `ParseClaudeStream()`: Converts full raw Claude output\n      - Handles event types: assistant, result, content_block_delta, content_block_start\n      - Extracts tool calls and formats them readably\n      - Filters protocol-level events\n\n### **CLI Log Streaming**\n\n12. **`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`** (excerpt)\n    - CLI client consumes SSE logs\n    - Sets header: `Accept: text/event-stream`\n    - Reads SSE events line-by-line\n    - Terminates on `event: done` event\n\n---\n\n## Key Features Summary\n\n### **SSE Log Streaming**\n- Route: `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Content-Type: `text/event-stream`\n- Headers: Cache-Control: no-cache, Connection: keep-alive, X-Accel-Buffering: no\n- Active runs: Live streaming via broadcaster pattern\n- Completed runs: Archived full.log file replay\n- Terminal event: `event: done\\ndata: {state}\\n\\n`\n\n### **Log Format**\n- Structured: `[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build`\n- Types: `status`, `script`, `llm`, custom\n- JSON payload with: `timestamp`, `type`, `content`, `step_name` (optional)\n\n### **Frontend Features**\n- EventSource API for real-time log updates\n- Auto-scroll on new content (can be disabled by user scroll-up)\n- Color-coded log types (status=blue, llm=green, script=text)\n- Live/Complete status badge with color transitions\n- Expandable step outputs with lazy loading\n- Container state monitoring\n- Run cancellation\n- Container deletion\n\n### **Patterns & Technologies**\n- **Server-Sent Events (SSE)**: Unidirectional server-to-client streaming\n- **EventSource API**: Browser native event streaming consumer\n- **Broadcaster Pattern**: Thread-safe pub/sub for multiple concurrent viewers\n- **JSON Log Lines**: Marshaled as SSE data events\n- **Polling Fallback**: For non-streaming data (steps, container status, run state)\n- **HTML Template Embedding**: Go `embed.FS` for static files and templates\n\n---\n\n## File Locations (Absolute Paths)\n\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css\n/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go\n/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go\n/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8681a56bdc5a821c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54948\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 50780</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76af65e3-c28d-44bf-af6f-261a8ed5d566","uuid":"01807f5b-5d28-4747-888b-53498be7e6b6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all web UI related files in this project, especially anything related to:\n1. SSE (Server-Sent Events) log streaming\n2. HTML templates with log display\n3. JavaScript that handles log updates\n4. Web server handlers for logs\n\nSearch thoroughly across the entire codebase. Look for patterns like \"text/event-stream\", \"EventSource\", \"SSE\", \"scroll\", \"logs\", HTML templates, JS files, and web handlers.","agentId":"a8681a56bdc5a821c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Web UI Related Files - Complete Inventory\n\n### Summary\nThe Cloche project implements a comprehensive web dashboard with Server-Sent Events (SSE) streaming for live log display. Here's the complete breakdown of all web UI related files:\n\n---\n\n## Files Found\n\n### **Core Web Infrastructure**\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** (49.1KB)\n   - Main HTTP request handler\n   - **SSE Streaming Handler**: `handleAPIStream()` (lines 805-871)\n     - Serves live log streams via Server-Sent Events\n     - Sets headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`\n     - Handles both active (live) and completed runs\n     - For active runs: subscribes to broadcaster and streams live events\n     - For completed runs: reads archived full.log file\n   - **Full Log Streaming**: `streamFullLog()` (lines 876-898)\n     - Reads `.cloche/{run-id}/output/full.log` files\n     - Parses log lines in format: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n     - Sends each line as SSE data event\n   - **Log Parsing**: \n     - `parseFullLogLine()` (lines 916-931): Parses structured log format with regex\n     - `parseLLMLogLine()` (lines 904-914): Parses Claude LLM stream JSON\n   - **Log regex pattern**: `