l-level events\n\n### **CLI Log Streaming**\n\n12. **`/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`** (excerpt)\n    - CLI client consumes SSE logs\n    - Sets header: `Accept: text/event-stream`\n    - Reads SSE events line-by-line\n    - Terminates on `event: done` event\n\n---\n\n## Key Features Summary\n\n### **SSE Log Streaming**\n- Route: `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Content-Type: `text/event-stream`\n- Headers: Cache-Control: no-cache, Connection: keep-alive, X-Accel-Buffering: no\n- Active runs: Live streaming via broadcaster pattern\n- Completed runs: Archived full.log file replay\n- Terminal event: `event: done\\ndata: {state}\\n\\n`\n\n### **Log Format**\n- Structured: `[2026-03-03T10:15:00Z] [status] step_started: build`\n- Types: `status`, `script`, `llm`, custom\n- JSON payload with: `timestamp`, `type`, `content`, `step_name` (optional)\n\n### **Frontend Features**\n- EventSource API for real-time log updates\n- Auto-scroll on new content (can be disabled by user scroll-up)\n- Color-coded log types (status=blue, llm=green, script=text)\n- Live/Complete status badge with color transitions\n- Expandable step outputs with lazy loading\n- Container state monitoring\n- Run cancellation\n- Container deletion\n\n### **Patterns & Technologies**\n- **Server-Sent Events (SSE)**: Unidirectional server-to-client streaming\n- **EventSource API**: Browser native event streaming consumer\n- **Broadcaster Pattern**: Thread-safe pub/sub for multiple concurrent viewers\n- **JSON Log Lines**: Marshaled as SSE data events\n- **Polling Fallback**: For non-streaming data (steps, container status, run state)\n- **HTML Template Embedding**: Go `embed.FS` for static files and templates\n\n---\n\n## File Locations (Absolute Paths)\n\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_