{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Fo23vJtDJDZ4qa173pkZDM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{{define \"content\"}}\n     2→<h1>\n     3→    <a href=\"/runs\">Runs</a> /\n     4→    {{if .ParentRun}}<a href=\"/runs/{{.ParentRun.ID}}\" class=\"parent-run-link\">{{.ParentRun.ID}}</a> / {{end}}\n     5→    {{.Run.ID}}\n     6→    <span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .Run.State}}\">{{.Run.State}}</span>\n     7→    {{if or (eq .Run.State \"pending\") (eq .Run.State \"running\")}}\n     8→    <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"cancel-run-btn\" onclick=\"cancelRun('{{.Run.ID}}')\" style=\"margin-left:0.5rem;\">Cancel</button>\n     9→    {{end}}\n    10→</h1>\n    11→\n    12→<div class=\"run-meta\">\n    13→    <dl>\n    14→        {{if .Run.Title}}<dt>Title</dt><dd>{{.Run.Title}}</dd>{{end}}\n    15→        {{if .ParentRun}}<dt>Parent Run</dt><dd><a href=\"/runs/{{.ParentRun.ID}}\">{{.ParentRun.ID}}</a> <span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .ParentRun.State}}\">{{.ParentRun.State}}</span></dd>{{end}}\n    16→        <dt>Workflow</dt><dd>{{.Run.WorkflowName}}</dd>\n    17→        <dt>Type</dt><dd>{{if .Run.IsHost}}host{{else}}container{{end}}</dd>\n    18→        <dt>Started</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.StartedAt}}</dd>\n    19→        <dt>Completed</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.CompletedAt}}</dd>\n    20→        <dt>Container</dt><dd class=\"mono\">{{.Run.ContainerID}}</dd>\n    21→        <dt>Container Status</dt>\n    22→        <dd id=\"container-status\">\n    23→            {{if eq .ContainerState \"running\"}}\n    24→                <span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>\n    25→            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"stopped\"}}\n    26→                <span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>\n    27→                {{if or (eq .Run.State \"succeeded\") (eq .Run.State \"failed\") (eq .Run.State \"cancelled\")}}\n    28→                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n    29→                {{end}}\n    30→            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"available\"}}\n    31→                <span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>\n    32→                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n    33→            {{else}}\n    34→                <span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>\n    35→            {{end}}\n    36→        </dd>\n    37→    </dl>\n    38→</div>\n    39→\n    40→{{if .Run.ErrorMessage}}\n    41→<div class=\"error-box\">{{.Run.ErrorMessage}}</div>\n    42→{{end}}\n    43→\n    44→{{if .ChildRuns}}\n    45→<h2>Child Runs</h2>\n    46→<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    47→    <thead>\n    48→        <tr>\n    49→            <th>Run ID</th>\n    50→            <th>Title</th>\n    51→            <th>Workflow</th>\n    52→            <th>State</th>\n    53→            <th>Started</th>\n    54→            <th>Completed</th>\n    55→        </tr>\n    56→    </thead>\n    57→    <tbody>\n    58→        {{range .ChildRuns}}\n    59→        <tr>\n    60→            <td><a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">{{.ID}}</a></td>\n    61→            <td>{{truncate .Title 50}}</td>\n    62→            <td>{{.WorkflowName}}</td>\n    63→            <td><span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .State}}\">{{.State}}</span></td>\n    64→            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n    65→            <td>{{formatTime .CompletedAt}}</td>\n    66→        </tr>\n    67→        {{end}}\n    68→    </tbody>\n    69→</table>\n    70→{{end}}\n    71→\n    72→<h2>Steps</h2>\n    73→<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    74→    <thead>\n    75→        <tr>\n    76→            <th>Step</th>\n    77→            <th>Result</th>\n    78→            <th>Started</th>\n    79→            <th>Duration</th>\n    80→        </tr>\n    81→    </thead>\n    82→    <tbody id=\"steps-body\">\n    83→    {{if .Steps}}\n    84→        {{range .Steps}}\n    85→        <tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"{{$.Run.ID}}\" data-step=\"{{.StepName}}\" data-index=\"{{.Index}}\">\n    86→            <td>{{.StepName}}</td>\n    87→            <td>{{if .Result}}<span class=\"badge badge-{{if eq .Result \"success\"}}succeeded{{else if eq .Result \"fail\"}}failed{{else}}pending{{end}}\">{{.Result}}</span>{{else}}<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>{{end}}</td>\n    88→            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n    89→            <td>{{.Duration}}</td>\n    90→        </tr>\n    91→        <tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"output-{{.Index}}\" style=\"display:none\">\n    92→            <td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>\n    93→        </tr>\n    94→        {{end}}\n    95→    {{else}}\n    96→        <tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>\n    97→    {{end}}\n    98→    </tbody>\n    99→</table>\n   100→\n   101→<h2>\n   102→    Log\n   103→    <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\" style=\"font-size:0.7rem; margin-left:0.5rem;\">Live</span>\n   104→</h2>\n   105→<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\"><pre id=\"log-content\"></pre></div>\n   106→{{end}}\n   107→\n   108→{{define \"scripts\"}}\n   109→<script>\n   110→(function() {\n   111→    var runState = '{{.Run.State}}';\n   112→    var runID = '{{.Run.ID}}';\n   113→\n   114→    // --- Log Viewer ---\n   115→    var logContent = document.getElementById('log-content');\n   116→    var logViewer = document.getElementById('log-viewer');\n   117→    var logStatus = document.getElementById('log-status');\n   118→    var autoScroll = true;\n   119→\n   120→    // Track scroll position to enable/disable auto-scroll\n   121→    logViewer.addEventListener('scroll', function() {\n   122→        var atBottom = logViewer.scrollHeight - logViewer.scrollTop - logViewer.clientHeight < 40;\n   123→        autoScroll = atBottom;\n   124→    });\n   125→\n   126→    function appendLogLine(line) {\n   127→        var span = document.createElement('span');\n   128→        span.className = 'log-line log-type-' + (line.type || 'script');\n   129→        span.textContent = '[' + line.timestamp + '] [' + line.type + '] ' + line.content + '\\n';\n   130→        logContent.appendChild(span);\n   131→        if (autoScroll) {\n   132→            logViewer.scrollTop = logViewer.scrollHeight;\n   133→        }\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    function markComplete() {\n   137→        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n   138→        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n   139→    }\n   140→\n   141→    // Connect to SSE stream\n   142→    var source = new EventSource('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stream');\n   143→    source.onmessage = function(e) {\n   144→        try {\n   145→            var line = JSON.parse(e.data);\n   146→            appendLogLine(line);\n   147→        } catch(err) {}\n   148→    };\n   149→    source.addEventListener('done', function(e) {\n   150→        markComplete();\n   151→        source.close();\n   152→    });\n   153→    source.onerror = function() {\n   154→        markComplete();\n   155→        source.close();\n   156→    };\n   157→\n   158→    // If already complete, mark the badge immediately\n   159→    if (runState === 'succeeded' || runState === 'failed' || runState === 'cancelled') {\n   160→        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n   161→        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    // --- Steps Polling (for active runs) ---\n   165→    if (runState !== 'succeeded' && runState !== 'failed' && runState !== 'cancelled') {\n   166→        function poll() {\n   167→            fetch('/api/runs/' + runID)\n   168→                .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n   169→                .then(function(data) {\n   170→                    if (data.state !== runState) {\n   171→                        location.reload();\n   172→                        return;\n   173→                    }\n   174→                    // Update container status\n   175→                    var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n   176→                    if (statusEl && data.container_state) {\n   177→                        var cs = data.container_state;\n   178→                        if (cs === 'running') {\n   179→                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>';\n   180→                        } else if (cs === 'stopped') {\n   181→                            var stoppedHtml = '<span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>';\n   182→                            if (data.state === 'succeeded' || data.state === 'failed' || data.state === 'cancelled') {\n   183→                                stoppedHtml += ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n   184→                            }\n   185→                            statusEl.innerHTML = stoppedHtml;\n   186→                        } else if (cs === 'available') {\n   187→                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>' +\n   188→                                ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n   189→                        } else {\n   190→                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n   191→                        }\n   192→                    }\n   193→                    var tbody = document.getElementById('steps-body');\n   194→                    if (!data.steps || data.steps.length === 0) {\n   195→                        tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>';\n   196→                        return;\n   197→                    }\n   198→\n   199→                    // Capture current accordion state before updating\n   200→                    var openAccordions = {};\n   201→                    var loadedOutputs = {};\n   202→                    var outputRows = tbody.querySelectorAll('.output-row');\n   203→                    for (var j = 0; j < outputRows.length; j++) {\n   204→                        var id = outputRows[j].id;\n   205→                        if (outputRows[j].style.display !== 'none') {\n   206→                            openAccordions[id] = true;\n   207→                        }\n   208→                        var pre = outputRows[j].querySelector('.step-output');\n   209→                        if (pre && pre.textContent !== 'Loading...') {\n   210→                            loadedOutputs[id] = pre.textContent;\n   211→                        }\n   212→                    }\n   213→\n   214→                    // Build updated step rows, preserving accordion state\n   215→                    var html = '';\n   216→                    for (var i = 0; i < data.steps.length; i++) {\n   217→                        var s = data.steps[i];\n   218→                        var badge = '';\n   219→                        if (s.result) {\n   220→                            var cls = s.result === 'success' ? 'succeeded' : s.result === 'fail' ? 'failed' : 'pending';\n   221→                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-' + cls + '\">' + escapeHtml(s.result) + '</span>';\n   222→                        } else {\n   223→                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>';\n   224→                        }\n   225→                        var outputId = 'output-' + i;\n   226→                        var isOpen = openAccordions[outputId];\n   227→                        html += '<tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\" data-step=\"' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '\" data-index=\"' + i + '\">' +\n   228→                            '<td>' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '</td>' +\n   229→                            '<td>' + badge + '</td>' +\n   230→                            '<td>' + s.started_at + '</td>' +\n   231→                            '<td>' + s.duration + '</td>' +\n   232→                            '</tr>' +\n   233→                            '<tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"' + outputId + '\"' + (isOpen ? '' : ' style=\"display:none\"') + '>' +\n   234→                            '<td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>' +\n   235→                            '</tr>';\n   236→                    }\n   237→                    tbody.innerHTML = html;\n   238→\n   239→                    // Restore loaded output content for open accordions\n   240→                    for (var key in loadedOutputs) {\n   241→                        var row = document.getElementById(key);\n   242→                        if (row) {\n   243→                            var pre = row.querySelector('.step-output');\n   244→                            if (pre) {\n   245→                                pre.textContent = loadedOutputs[key];\n   246→                            }\n   247→                        }\n   248→                    }\n   249→\n   250→                    // Re-fetch output for accordions that were open but had no cached content\n   251→                    for (var key in openAccordions) {\n   252→                        if (!loadedOutputs[key]) {\n   253→                            var row = document.getElementById(key);\n   254→                            if (row) {\n   255→                                var stepRow = row.previousElementSibling;\n   256→                                if (stepRow && stepRow.dataset.runId && stepRow.dataset.step) {\n   257→                                    (function(r, rid, sname) {\n   258→                                        var pre = r.querySelector('.step-output');\n   259→                                        fetch('/api/runs/' + rid + '/steps/' + sname + '/output')\n   260→                                            .then(function(resp) {\n   261→                                                if (!resp.ok) return 'No output available.';\n   262→                                                return resp.text();\n   263→                                            })\n   264→                                            .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n   265→                                            .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n   266→                                    })(row, stepRow.dataset.runId, stepRow.dataset.step);\n   267→                                }\n   268→                            }\n   269→                        }\n   270→                    }\n   271→                })\n   272→                .catch(function() {});\n   273→        }\n   274→        setInterval(poll, 2000);\n   275→    }\n   276→\n   277→    function escapeHtml(s) {\n   278→        if (!s) return '';\n   279→        var d = document.createElement('div');\n   280→        d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n   281→        return d.innerHTML;\n   282→    }\n   283→})();\n   284→\n   285→// Cancel run\n   286→    window.cancelRun = function(runID) {\n   287→        var btn = document.getElementById('cancel-run-btn');\n   288→        if (btn) btn.disabled = true;\n   289→        fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stop', { method: 'POST' })\n   290→            .then(function(r) { return r.json().then(function(d) { return {ok: r.ok, data: d}; }); })\n   291→            .then(function(res) {\n   292→                if (res.ok) {\n   293→                    location.reload();\n   294→                } else {\n   295→                    if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n   296→                    alert('Failed to cancel run: ' + (res.data.error || 'unknown error'));\n   297→                }\n   298→            })\n   299→            .catch(function() {\n   300→                if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n   301→                alert('Failed to cancel run');\n   302→            });\n   303→    };\n   304→\n   305→// Delete container\n   306→    window.deleteContainer = function(runID) {\n   307→        var btn = document.getElementById('delete-container-btn');\n   308→        if (btn) btn.disabled = true;\n   309→        fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/container', { method: 'DELETE' })\n   310→            .then(function(r) { return r.json().then(function(d) { return {ok: r.ok, data: d}; }); })\n   311→            .then(function(res) {\n   312→                var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n   313→                if (res.ok) {\n   314→                    statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n   315→                } else {\n   316→                    if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n   317→                    alert('Failed to delete container: ' + (res.data.error || 'unknown error'));\n   318→                }\n   319→            })\n   320→            .catch(function() {\n   321→                if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n   322→                alert('Failed to delete container');\n   323→            });\n   324→    };\n   325→\n   326→    // Toggle step output rows\n   327→document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n   328→    var row = e.target.closest('.step-row');\n   329→    if (!row) return;\n   330→    var idx = row.dataset.index;\n   331→    var outputRow = document.getElementById('output-' + idx);\n   332→    if (!outputRow) return;\n   333→\n   334→    if (outputRow.style.display === 'none') {\n   335→        outputRow.style.display = '';\n   336→        var pre = outputRow.querySelector('.step-output');\n   337→        if (pre.textContent === 'Loading...') {\n   338→            var runId = row.dataset.runId;\n   339→            var step = row.dataset.step;\n   340→            fetch('/api/runs/' + runId + '/steps/' + step + '/output')\n   341→                .then(function(r) {\n   342→                    if (!r.ok) return 'No output available.';\n   343→                    return r.text();\n   344→                })\n   345→                .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n   346→                .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n   347→        }\n   348→    } else {\n   349→        outputRow.style.display = 'none';\n   350→    }\n   351→});\n   352→</script>\n   353→{{end}}\n   354→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76af65e3-c28d-44bf-af6f-261a8ed5d566","uuid":"342522d9-17bc-4904-9a0b-35783b3b55be","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html","content":"{{define \"content\"}}\n<h1>\n    <a href=\"/runs\">Runs</a> /\n    {{if .ParentRun}}<a href=\"/runs/{{.ParentRun.ID}}\" class=\"parent-run-link\">{{.ParentRun.ID}}</a> / {{end}}\n    {{.Run.ID}}\n    <span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .Run.State}}\">{{.Run.State}}</span>\n    {{if or (eq .Run.State \"pending\") (eq .Run.State \"running\")}}\n    <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"cancel-run-btn\" onclick=\"cancelRun('{{.Run.ID}}')\" style=\"margin-left:0.5rem;\">Cancel</button>\n    {{end}}\n</h1>\n\n<div class=\"run-meta\">\n    <dl>\n        {{if .Run.Title}}<dt>Title</dt><dd>{{.Run.Title}}</dd>{{end}}\n        {{if .ParentRun}}<dt>Parent Run</dt><dd><a href=\"/runs/{{.ParentRun.ID}}\">{{.ParentRun.ID}}</a> <span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .ParentRun.State}}\">{{.ParentRun.State}}</span></dd>{{end}}\n        <dt>Workflow</dt><dd>{{.Run.WorkflowName}}</dd>\n        <dt>Type</dt><dd>{{if .Run.IsHost}}host{{else}}container{{end}}</dd>\n        <dt>Started</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.StartedAt}}</dd>\n        <dt>Completed</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.CompletedAt}}</dd>\n        <dt>Container</dt><dd class=\"mono\">{{.Run.ContainerID}}</dd>\n        <dt>Container Status</dt>\n        <dd id=\"container-status\">\n            {{if eq .ContainerState \"running\"}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>\n            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"stopped\"}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>\n                {{if or (eq .Run.State \"succeeded\") (eq .Run.State \"failed\") (eq .Run.State \"cancelled\")}}\n                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n                {{end}}\n            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"available\"}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>\n                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n            {{else}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>\n            {{end}}\n        </dd>\n    </dl>\n</div>\n\n{{if .Run.ErrorMessage}}\n<div class=\"error-box\">{{.Run.ErrorMessage}}</div>\n{{end}}\n\n{{if .ChildRuns}}\n<h2>Child Runs</h2>\n<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    <thead>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Run ID</th>\n            <th>Title</th>\n            <th>Workflow</th>\n            <th>State</th>\n            <th>Started</th>\n            <th>Completed</th>\n        </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n        {{range .ChildRuns}}\n        <tr>\n            <td><a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">{{.ID}}</a></td>\n            <td>{{truncate .Title 50}}</td>\n            <td>{{.WorkflowName}}</td>\n            <td><span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .State}}\">{{.State}}</span></td>\n            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n            <td>{{formatTime .CompletedAt}}</td>\n        </tr>\n        {{end}}\n    </tbody>\n</table>\n{{end}}\n\n<h2>Steps</h2>\n<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    <thead>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Step</th>\n            <th>Result</th>\n            <th>Started</th>\n            <th>Duration</th>\n        </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody id=\"steps-body\">\n    {{if .Steps}}\n        {{range .Steps}}\n        <tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"{{$.Run.ID}}\" data-step=\"{{.StepName}}\" data-index=\"{{.Index}}\">\n            <td>{{.StepName}}</td>\n            <td>{{if .Result}}<span class=\"badge badge-{{if eq .Result \"success\"}}succeeded{{else if eq .Result \"fail\"}}failed{{else}}pending{{end}}\">{{.Result}}</span>{{else}}<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>{{end}}</td>\n            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n            <td>{{.Duration}}</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"output-{{.Index}}\" style=\"display:none\">\n            <td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>\n        </tr>\n        {{end}}\n    {{else}}\n        <tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>\n    {{end}}\n    </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>\n    Log\n    <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\" style=\"font-size:0.7rem; margin-left:0.5rem;\">Live</span>\n</h2>\n<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\"><pre id=\"log-content\"></pre></div>\n{{end}}\n\n{{define \"scripts\"}}\n<script>\n(function() {\n    var runState = '{{.Run.State}}';\n    var runID = '{{.Run.ID}}';\n\n    // --- Log Viewer ---\n    var logContent = document.getElementById('log-content');\n    var logViewer = document.getElementById('log-viewer');\n    var logStatus = document.getElementById('log-status');\n    var autoScroll = true;\n\n    // Track scroll position to enable/disable auto-scroll\n    logViewer.addEventListener('scroll', function() {\n        var atBottom = logViewer.scrollHeight - logViewer.scrollTop - logViewer.clientHeight < 40;\n        autoScroll = atBottom;\n    });\n\n    function appendLogLine(line) {\n        var span = document.createElement('span');\n        span.className = 'log-line log-type-' + (line.type || 'script');\n        span.textContent = '[' + line.timestamp + '] [' + line.type + '] ' + line.content + '\\n';\n        logContent.appendChild(span);\n        if (autoScroll) {\n            logViewer.scrollTop = logViewer.scrollHeight;\n        }\n    }\n\n    function markComplete() {\n        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n    }\n\n    // Connect to SSE stream\n    var source = new EventSource('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stream');\n    source.onmessage = function(e) {\n        try {\n            var line = JSON.parse(e.data);\n            appendLogLine(line);\n        } catch(err) {}\n    };\n    source.addEventListener('done', function(e) {\n        markComplete();\n        source.close();\n    });\n    source.onerror = function() {\n        markComplete();\n        source.close();\n    };\n\n    // If already complete, mark the badge immediately\n    if (runState === 'succeeded' || runState === 'failed' || runState === 'cancelled') {\n        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n    }\n\n    // --- Steps Polling (for active runs) ---\n    if (runState !== 'succeeded' && runState !== 'failed' && runState !== 'cancelled') {\n        function poll() {\n            fetch('/api/runs/' + runID)\n                .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n                .then(function(data) {\n                    if (data.state !== runState) {\n                        location.reload();\n                        return;\n                    }\n                    // Update container status\n                    var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n                    if (statusEl && data.container_state) {\n                        var cs = data.container_state;\n                        if (cs === 'running') {\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>';\n                        } else if (cs === 'stopped') {\n                            var stoppedHtml = '<span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>';\n                            if (data.state === 'succeeded' || data.state === 'failed' || data.state === 'cancelled') {\n                                stoppedHtml += ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n                            }\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = stoppedHtml;\n                        } else if (cs === 'available') {\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>' +\n                                ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n                        } else {\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n                        }\n                    }\n                    var tbody = document.getElementById('steps-body');\n                    if (!data.steps || data.steps.length === 0) {\n                        tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>';\n                        return;\n                    }\n\n                    // Capture current accordion state before updating\n                    var openAccordions = {};\n                    var loadedOutputs = {};\n                    var outputRows = tbody.querySelectorAll('.output-row');\n                    for (var j = 0; j < outputRows.length; j++) {\n                        var id = outputRows[j].id;\n                        if (outputRows[j].style.display !== 'none') {\n                            openAccordions[id] = true;\n                        }\n                        var pre = outputRows[j].querySelector('.step-output');\n                        if (pre && pre.textContent !== 'Loading...') {\n                            loadedOutputs[id] = pre.textContent;\n                        }\n                    }\n\n                    // Build updated step rows, preserving accordion state\n                    var html = '';\n                    for (var i = 0; i < data.steps.length; i++) {\n                        var s = data.steps[i];\n                        var badge = '';\n                        if (s.result) {\n                            var cls = s.result === 'success' ? 'succeeded' : s.result === 'fail' ? 'failed' : 'pending';\n                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-' + cls + '\">' + escapeHtml(s.result) + '</span>';\n                        } else {\n                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>';\n                        }\n                        var outputId = 'output-' + i;\n                        var isOpen = openAccordions[outputId];\n                        html += '<tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\" data-step=\"' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '\" data-index=\"' + i + '\">' +\n                            '<td>' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '</td>' +\n                            '<td>' + badge + '</td>' +\n                            '<td>' + s.started_at + '</td>' +\n                            '<td>' + s.duration + '</td>' +\n                            '</tr>' +\n                            '<tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"' + outputId + '\"' + (isOpen ? '' : ' style=\"display:none\"') + '>' +\n                            '<td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>' +\n                            '</tr>';\n                    }\n                    tbody.innerHTML = html;\n\n                    // Restore loaded output content for open accordions\n                    for (var key in loadedOutputs) {\n                        var row = document.getElementById(key);\n                        if (row) {\n                            var pre = row.querySelector('.step-output');\n                            if (pre) {\n                                pre.textContent = loadedOutputs[key];\n                            }\n                        }\n                    }\n\n                    // Re-fetch output for accordions that were open but had no cached content\n                    for (var key in openAccordions) {\n                        if (!loadedOutputs[key]) {\n                            var row = document.getElementById(key);\n                            if (row) {\n                                var stepRow = row.previousElementSibling;\n                                if (stepRow && stepRow.dataset.runId && stepRow.dataset.step) {\n                                    (function(r, rid, sname) {\n                                        var pre = r.querySelector('.step-output');\n                                        fetch('/api/runs/' + rid + '/steps/' + sname + '/output')\n                                            .then(function(resp) {\n                                                if (!resp.ok) return 'No output available.';\n                                                return resp.text();\n                                            })\n                                            .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n                                            .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n                                    })(row, stepRow.dataset.runId, stepRow.dataset.step);\n                                }\n                            }\n                        }\n                    }\n                })\n                .catch(function() {});\n        }\n        setInterval(poll, 2000);\n    }\n\n    function escapeHtml(s) {\n        if (!s) return '';\n        var d = document.createElement('div');\n        d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n        return d.innerHTML;\n    }\n})();\n\n// Cancel run\n    window.cancelRun = function(runID) {\n        var btn = document.getElementById('cancel-run-btn');\n        if (btn) btn.disabled = true;\n        fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stop', { method: 'POST' })\n            .then(function(r) { return r.json().then(function(d) { return {ok: r.ok, data: d}; }); })\n            .then(function(res) {\n                if (res.ok) {\n                    location.reload();\n                } else {\n                    if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n                    alert('Failed to cancel run: ' + (res.data.error || 'unknown error'));\n                }\n            })\n            .catch(function() {\n                if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n                alert('Failed to cancel run');\n            });\n    };\n\n// Delete container\n    window.deleteContainer = function(runID) {\n        var btn = document.getElementById('delete-container-btn');\n        if (btn) btn.disabled = true;\n        fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/container', { method: 'DELETE' })\n            .then(function(r) { return r.json().then(function(d) { return {ok: r.ok, data: d}; }); })\n            .then(function(res) {\n                var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n                if (res.ok) {\n                    statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n                } else {\n                    if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n                    alert('Failed to delete container: ' + (res.data.error || 'unknown error'));\n                }\n            })\n            .catch(function() {\n                if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n                alert('Failed to delete container');\n            });\n    };\n\n    // Toggle step output rows\ndocument.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n    var row = e.target.closest('.step-row');\n    if (!row) return;\n    var idx = row.dataset.index;\n    var outputRow = document.getElementById('output-' + idx);\n    if (!outputRow) return;\n\n    if (outputRow.style.display === 'none') {\n        outputRow.style.display = '';\n        var pre = outputRow.querySelector('.step-output');\n        if (pre.textContent === 'Loading...') {\n            var runId = row.dataset.runId;\n            var step = row.dataset.step;\n            fetch('/api/runs/' + runId + '/steps/' + step + '/output')\n                .then(function(r) {\n                    if (!r.ok) return 'No output available.';\n                    return r.text();\n                })\n                .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n                .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n        }\n    } else {\n        outputRow.style.display = 'none';\n    }\n});\n</script>\n{{end}}\n","numLines":354,"startLine":1,"totalLines":354}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017iQVNFe1vuKv2vhhnx7r76","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current code. Let me analyze the scroll behavior:\n\n1. There's already an `autoScroll` variable initialized to `true` (line 118)\n2. There's a scroll event listener that sets `autoScroll` based on whether the user is near the bottom (line 121-124)\n3. In `appendLogLine`, if `autoScroll` is true, it scrolls to the bottom (lines 131-133)\n\nSo the basic auto-scroll logic exists. But the issue says \"SSE log events reset the scroll position.\" Let me think about what could cause the scroll position to reset...\n\nLooking more carefully at the code, I see the `appendLogLine` function appends a span to `logContent` (the `<pre>` element inside the log-viewer div). \n\nWhen new content gets added to the DOM, the scroll position shouldn't automatically reset—`scrollTop` should stay stable. But I'm wondering if there's a full page reload happening somewhere. Looking at the poll function, there's a `location.reload()` call when the run state changes, though that's a separate issue. The real problem might be in the SSE handler—when EventSource reconnects automatically after an error, it could restart streaming all logs for completed runs, which would cause the scroll to jump around.\n\nLet me check the server-side handler for the stream to understand what's actually being sent.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5500,"cache_read_input_tokens":17432,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5500},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76af65e3-c28d-44bf-af6f-261a8ed5d566","uuid":"11ff1a7a-6c6d-4194-baa7-aaf09472f408"}
